lines.text: you, you who has smiled when you're in pain
you who has soldiered through the profane
they were distracted and shut down
why would you talk to me at all
such words were dishon'rable and in vain
their promise as solid as a fog
i'll be your keeper for life
i'll be your warrior of care
i'll be your angel on call,
you, you in the chaos feigning sane
you, you who has pushed beyond what's humane
and where was your watchman then
i'll be your keeper for life
i'll be your warrior of care
i'll be your angel on call,
now no more smiling mid crestfall
no more holding still in the hailstorm
i'll be your keeper for life
i'll be your warrior of care
i'll be your angel on call,
